4. Data Acquisition and Cleaning/Preprocessing:  
4.1 Data Acquisition and Initial Load:  
The dataset was loaded into a Pandas DataFrame using the read_csv() 
4.2 Data Cleaning 
● The dataset contained no missing values, so no imputation was required. 
● Categorical features were converted into numerical format, suitable for machine learning models. 
● Binary variables like Weekend and Revenue were encoded as:  
○ False - 0, True - 1 
● The VisitorType feature was encoded as: 
○ Returning_Visitor - 0 
○ New_Visitor - 1 
○ Other - 2 
● The Month feature was numerically encoded based on calendar order as follows: Feb = 2, Mar = 3, 
May = 5, June = 6, Jul = 7, Aug = 8, Sep = 9, Oct = 10, Nov = 11, and Dec = 12. 
These cleaning steps ensured the dataset was consistent, machine-readable, and ready for preprocessing 
and model training. 
5. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) 
Analysis of browsing behavior through histograms and correlation matrices revealed that PageValues is by far 
the strongest predictor of Revenue. Sessions with high PageValues and long ProductRelated_Duration exhibit 
significantly higher purchase probability. ExitRates and BounceRates show negative correlation with 
Revenue, confirming that users leaving quickly are unlikely to convert. Weekend traffic tends to be slightly 
lower in conversion compared with weekday sessions. 
