5.2 Handling Data Imbalance 
To address this imbalance, SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Over-sampling Technique) was applied. SMOTE 
generates synthetic samples for the minority class (Revenue = 1), helping to balance the dataset. This 
improves model learning, reduces bias toward the majority class, and enhances the performance of 
classification models. 
